Philippine Stocks: Atlas, Bank of Philippine Islands, Philex

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-19T04:46:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/philippine-stocks-atlas-consolidated-dmci-philex-mining-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.1 percent to
4,297.93.  Copper producers:  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the largest
Philippine producer of the metal, jumped 2.6 percent to 19.80
pesos, the highest close based on prices going back to January
1990.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp
increased 1.1 percent to 17.40 pesos, snapping a two-day loss.  Copper rose in  New York , capping the longest rally in three
months, on bets that demand will climb in  China , the world’s
biggest consumer of industrial metals.  Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)   advanced 1.5
percent to 58.15 pesos, taking its two-day gain to 2.9 percent.
It’s the stock’s biggest two-day rally since April 4. The lender
said it will pay 90 centavos a share in dividends.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
